<p> 
Turtle graphics are a method of generating line-based pictures through the 
manipulation of a cursor, called the turtle.  The turtle has three attributes
</p>
<ol>
<li>
a position in a two-dimensional grid
</li>
<li>an direction that it is pointing, and</li>
<li>a pen (which may be up or down, a certain color, a certain thickness, etc).</li></ol>

